sharedPost.text:
Casting Call

Production: Mother's Ruin, by Steve Bird (Back by popular demand!)

The story so far in the life of Liverpool comedian Garry Skyner, one of Britain's first- born victims of the Thalidomide medical disaster. Steve Birds play is a moving and emotional, yet hard hitting play about the highs, lows, struggles and sheer determination of a loving Mother and her son who refused to be beaten by the Government and company that profited from this medical disaster.

We are looking for a talented female actor playing range 20-30ys, who is from Liverpool or can do a convincing accent, for the lead role of Frances, Gary's Mum.
Frances is a spirited, humourous woman, who whilst having a heart of gold, has an inner strength, is tough, and fights for her child and what is right.
If you believe you are what we are looking for please send you CV and headshot to elainestewart46@yahoo.com 

Auditions to take place on Sunday 21st September 1pm-3pm at a Liverpool venue to be disclosed on receipt of CV, and a script will be provided. 

Performances will take place at the Epstein Theatre on 27th and 28th February 2026.

You must be available for rehearsals Sundays 1pm- 4pm (in Liverpool) starting 2nd November.
*This is a profit share production

ðŸ“Œ Background Roles Needed:
 â€¢ Civilians (men, women, children)
 â€¢ Wounded civilians & refugees
 â€¢ Soldiers
 â€¢ Enemy soldiers

ðŸŽ¬ Production Dates:
 â€¢ October 25â€“26 (Principal)
 â€¢ November 1â€“2 (Principal)
 â€¢ November 8â€“9 (Principal)

This is a powerful production that explores survival, innocence, and resilience during war. Background performers will help bring authenticity and emotion to the world of the story.

ðŸ“ Location: Los Angeles area

â€¢ age

Iren Tovmasian

ROSTER CALL: ICT Productions (SAG-AFTRA & DGA Signatory)

My company, ICT Productions, is building a first-call roster across departments for upcoming narrative, branded, and live projects in Los Angeles.

Weâ€™re an award-winning company and Iâ€™ve personally managed $200M+ across network/broadcast productions (including the Super Bowl) and multiple films in active development.

This is not an invite for immediate work; itâ€™s an invite to join our vetted roster we call before any public search.

Departments (all levels welcome):

Production (Producers, UPM/PM, Coordinators)
AD Dept
Script Supervisor
Camera
G&E
Sound
Art/Set Dec
Props
Construction/Scenic
Wardrobe
Hair/Makeup
Locations
Stunts/Intimacy
SFX
Medics/Safety
Transportation
Video/DIT
VFX
Post (Editorial/Color/Sound/Score)
EPK/BTS
Crafty/Catering
Security

Email: jake@ictproductions.com

Subject: ICT Roster - [NAME]

â€¢ Role(s) + union status
â€¢ Base day rate + kit notes (if any)
â€¢ IMDb / Reel / Portfolio
â€¢ Home-base ZIP
â€¢ Best contact info
â€¢ Note if open to student/ultra-low projects

We run professional, safety-first, union-aligned sets with clear paperwork and on-time pay. 

Equal opportunity; all backgrounds encouraged to submit.

Thanks! Looking forward to meeting you.

Jake Crossman, Producer
ICT Productions, Los Angeles, CA
(747) 528-7818
jake@ictproductions.com

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 1st week in November 2025 (date tbc). For actors based in the London area.

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  25-35, 5â€™ 6â€+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of Â£300 for 15 hours. 

BACKGROUND MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 25-35, 5â€™ 6â€+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for Â£150 for 7 hours. 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

items.text:
Casting Call (Non-Union) for COUPLES/POLYCULES - Paid

Looking for actors to play the role of clients in a simulated therapy session. The video clips will be used in an online training system for counselors and psychologists. The sessions include some scripted elements to prepare, and then some improv with prompts.

We are currently interested in filming with mature couples, queer couples, interracial couples, or throuples/polycules of various gender identity combinations. All ages, all gender expressions/identities, all ethnicities, and persons with disabilities are welcome. 

All experience levels with acting are welcome, including experienced actors with less experienced partners. We are committed to making this a respectful and safe process, with open communication and respect for boundaries.

Comfortable English fluency is required.

Immediate filming dates are October 10 through 17, but more will occur in the future so please submit if you're interested at all.

Location is downtown Vancouver - Gastown. Pay is $90 CAD per performer, wit the expectation of some prepared material, duration: 1 hour

Please email phil@skillsetter.com with your headshot and resume. If you've submitted for a past session, you're welcome to submit again. We do sometimes receive more submissions than we are able to respond to, but we do read them all, and we do save your submissions for future consideration.

Drehort ist Berlin.

Was ich suche:

- Schauspielerin im Alter von 28 bis 44 Jahren  

- SpaÃŸ an geskripteten Szenen und klaren Rollenbildern  

- Offen fÃ¼r verschiedene Rollen (z. B. Freundin, Kollegin, Date, AffÃ¤re, Nachbarin etc.)  

- GefÃ¼hl fÃ¼r Timing, Mimik und Punchlines  

- Keine Angst vor Kamera, Humor oder Drama

- Kreative Zusammenarbeit mit einem Creator, der Storytelling & Timing liebt  

- Szenen mit klarer Struktur, aber Raum fÃ¼r eigene Ideen  

- MÃ¶glichkeit, dich als wiederkehrende Figur zu etablieren

items.text:
We are now casting for our Halloween Party show .

The show will tour into community based venues, Nursing and Residential Homes, Day Centres.

We are seeking self-contained experienced hardworking singer/ performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community.

The Dates

Rehearsals â€“17th and 18th October in London

Playing Dates-20th -31st October-

We work Monday to Friday only.

The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced engaging performers with great singing voices,

We are looking for drivers with cars only

Please confirm where you are based in your application.

We offer Â£700 per week plus fuel on the road .

We are also casting our one man / woman musical show Winter Wonderland that will tour care homes and community based throughout December.

The show is production style show based on songs from the musicals Mary Poppins, White Christmas, Singing In The Rain, The Wizard Of Oz As well as traditional Christmas songs and carols, comedy routines and festive entertainment for all.

Dates

Rehearsals 24th -28th November

Playing dates 1st-23rd December

We perform two 60 minute shows 6 days a week.

We are offering 600 .00 per week fuel on the road and accommodation allowance when required.

MUST BE A DRIVER WITH A CAR

Please email details including a singing reel to

info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

Hi everyone! I'm casting 'All-Round Champion', a CSA & Emmy Award-winning reality sports competition series that brings together 10 of the best youth athletes from across North America and the UK. Each season, these incredible athletes represent 10 different sports and face the ultimate challenge: competing in each other's disciplines for the title of All-Round Champion!

If you know any talented athletes between the ages of 11 and 18 who would thrive in this environment, I'd love for you to share this opportunity with them!

Interested athletes can apply here: [https://allroundchampion7.castingcrane.com](https://allroundchampion7.castingcrane.com/) - please note the deadline for submissions is early November, so don't delay!

Watch our Season 6 trailer to get a feel for the show: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GXbmDbRjQ24](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GXbmDbRjQ24)

Learn more about our production company: [https://blueantmedia.com/](https://blueantmedia.com/)

Email me your questions at [Jessica.mcgann@blueantmedia.com](mailto:Jessica.mcgann@blueantmedia.com)

Interested athletes can apply here: [https://allroundchampion7.castingcrane.com](https://allroundchampion7.castingcrane.com/) - please note the deadline for submissions is early November, so don't delay!

Watch our Season 6 trailer to get a feel for the show: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GXbmDbRjQ24](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GXbmDbRjQ24)

Learn more about our production company: [https://blueantmedia.com/](https://blueantmedia.com/)

Email me your questions at [Jessica.mcgann@blueantmedia.com](mailto:Jessica.mcgann@blueantmedia.com)

items.text:
Hello! We are shooting an unpaid improvised short film next week from the 15th to the 18th of October based on the concept for our feature film SOPHIE, and we are looking for an actor for one for the lead roles, to play a charismatic pubcrawl guide (25-35, Male) with a dark side. Shooting will take place on the 15th, 16th, 17th and 18th of October, all night shoots.

If you're interested in knowing more details please send me your showreel or a short introductory video of you and your acting experience, to vasco.cinema.2018@gmail.com.

Sinopsis: On a weekend escape to Copenhagen, Sophie reunites with an old friend and spirals through a night of fleeting connections, as sheâ€™s forced to confront the cost of trying to feel anything at all.

Saturday, November 8, 2025
Greenwood Oasis Theater â€“ 7621 S. Greenwood Ave, Chicago, IL
Showtime: 7 PM | VIP Experience: 4 PM | Doors Open: 6 PM
FREE PARKING

Come dressed in your best 40s, 50s, 60s, or 70s attire!
(Itâ€™s recommended â€” not required â€” for the full experience!)

Step back in time and experience a powerful musical journey through the Great Migration, Bronzevilleâ€™s rich Black history, and the soul of World War II-era Chicago â€” told through acting, singing, dancing, and narration.

 Featuring unforgettable portrayals of:
Billie Holiday, Nat King Cole, Ella Fitzgerald, Dinah Washington, Cab Calloway, Etta James
Plus a moving tribute to Minnie Riperton, Chicagoâ€™s own.

items.text:
**SHORT FILM CREW CALL -***** Beyond the Blue Light***

*ISO of lgbtq, bipoc, and immigrant filmmakers to fill the following positions. All details below. Students welcome!*

*PAID:*

Studio Teacher (one minor 8 or 9 years old)

*IMDB Credit, Copy, Meals, Gas Stipend:*

2nd AC

Key Grip 

G&E Swing

Costumer (+ materials stipend)

Boom OP

PA

**Synopsis:**

*Beyond the Blue Light* is an emotionally charged drama about the cost of apathy in the chronically online era told through the perspective of two trans latine immigrants. 

**Location:**

Los Angeles: Hollywood & North Hollywood

**Dates:**

11/1 - 11/4

**About the Director:**

Simone Brazzini is an award winning filmmaker from Lima, Peru and now based in Los Angeles. Their debut LA short will be making its world premiere at the Micheaux Film Festival. They were recently named in a Deadline article and is a Soho House x Creative Futures Mentee. Simone founded Vibes Video in 2021, a production company that creates radically authentic work across all genres with a focus on lgbtq, bipoc, and neurodiverse voices on and off camera. 

**To Submit:**

Please email a portfolio and/or resume to vibesvideoproductions@gmail.com AND CC productions.fakeid@gmail.com

**THANK YOU**

items.text: Beware this guy offering $2000 for voice acting absolute scam. He's been on multiple posts

sharedPost.text: Just a heads up re the posts offering 2000 dollars for voice acting .  This is a total scam from people trying to get your bank details . The recent guy who posted used a picture which has been used on countless sites . The first thing to do is use a reverse image site to see if the posters picture is genuine . If it seems too good to be true â€¦â€¦ it is!!! No one will be paying you 2000 dollars for your neutral English accent . I posted the image here on his post  and he disappeared pretty quickly . And they always use weird English names  like Williams (not William). You have been warned

**INDIAN / PAKISTANI ACTING TALENT WANTED**

**Must be London Based** - for a **PROFIT SHARE **fringe theatre production running 31st March to 4th April in South Kensington, London (see image).

**ROLES CURRENTLY AVAILABLE:**
* **ZAINAB (FEMALE/ 50s-60s) - **a fiercely charismatic Daily-Mail reading matriarch (Punjabi accent) *
* **IMRAN (MALE/ 30s-40s) - **a young father working as a corporate accountant (Burnley accent, can coach)
* **RANIA (FEMALE/ 20s-30s) - **Imran's rebellious wife (Burnley or Punjabi accent - talent also needs to be able to sing)
* **SAMIR (MALE/ 30s-40s) - **a heavily Anglicised London surgeon (RP)
* **FATHER (MALE/ 60s-70s) - **Zainab's intelligent, devoted and long-suffering husband*

* Zainab and Father talent are additionally paid Equity Minimum for a day's filming work

**Please email the director on ***reelpeoplefilms@hotmail.com*** for audition pieces and any further information. **Please note that this is a profit-share fringe production and renumeration (other than the filming aspect) depends on ticket sales.

My name is Luke Kenyon, and Iâ€™m a film student at SAE Liverpool. Weâ€™re currently working on a new short film project titled Last Night and are looking to cast two male-identifying actors (mid twenties)to join our team. This project is Non paid but we will be providing travel expenses as well as catering 

Shooting dates 9th - 15th November 2025 Liverpool, England

Synopsis -

On the anniversary of his best friendâ€™s suicide, Aaron plans to end his own life. He ignores his mothers phone calls and edges closer towards his own end, until he unexpectedly hears a knock at his apartment front door. His best friend, Ben, appears in an attempt to make amends and guide Aaron away from darkness. This intimate drama, through one final, raw conversation, forces Aaron to choose between following the same path that Ben took a year ago, or answering the call that could save him.

Aaron:

Aaron, mid 20's, slightly introverted and reserved. A complicated character with a lot going on in his mind. His low confidence makes it hard for him to open up to others about his feelings, especially about the loss of his best friend (Ben), who meant the world to him. He loves music and even used to play in a band with Ben. 

Ben:

Ben, mid 20's, soft and sensitive personality. His battles with his own mental health has led him to an unfortunate end, which ultimately, has hurt someone very close to him (Aaron), although this was never his intention. Benâ€™s aim is to make some sort of amends from his past actions and to help Aaron not make the same mistake that he did. 

If you have any questions about the project or roles, please donâ€™t hesitate to get in touch â€” Iâ€™m happy to provide more information.

If you  are interested in applying, please use one of the provided links below or alternatively email me at 120206uk@saeinstitute.edu with your details, previous work, or portfolio. (Including heat shots) please provide which role you are applying for 

Thank you very much for your time We look forward to hearing from you!

Kind regards,

Luke Kenyon

Film Student, SAE Institute

https://www.starnow.com/casting/last-night-3021254/

https://www.mandy.com/aa/project/3021242/last-night/

items.text:
Rainhill Garrick Society are performing â€˜ Habeus Corpusâ€™ by Alan Bennett on February 12th-14th 2026.

Alan Bennettâ€™s Habeus Corpus is set some time in the Seventies and follows the lives of the Wicksteed family. The story follows Dr and Muriel Wicksteed as they both seek pleasure and fun outside of their marital relationship. The farcical play is very fast paced, incredibly funny and occasionally surreal. The bumbling sex-obsessed British characters such as the virginal vicar, the ï¬‚at chested spinster, the peering doctor, his frustrated wife and of course a bra salesman man all come together in this bizarre and thoroughly entertaining story.

Parts available:-

Dennis Wicksteed - the hypochondriac son of Dr Wickseed, (20-30)

Felicity Rumpers - young, nubile, upper class  (20-30)

Constance Wicksteed - the sister of Dr Wicksteed, flat chested and sex starved, (20+) 

Sir Percy Shorter - chairman of the BMA, quite upper class and not too tall (Mid 40s+

Play read through Tuesday 21st October at 7.30 in Rainhill Village Hall

Auditions- Thursday 23rd October at 7.30 Rainhill Village Hall 

Rehearsals are on Tuesdays and Thursday evenings 7.30-9.30 and the 3 Sundays prior to the performance.

Audition pieces are available on request. 

We are an amateur group so the roles are unpaid, but we are a well respected group of 83 years standing who enjoy great support from a large dedicated audience. 

The play is great fun with some slapstick and music but with some poignant moments that say a lot about relationships.

For further information, contact: sophiebrogan99@gmail.com

Jigsaw Casting is looking for a George Washington lookalike in their mid 60â€™s for a Software Campaign across North America! 

Weâ€™re looking for MEN mid 60â€™s+ who bear an uncanny resemblance to George Washington. Have you ever been mistaken for the first president of the United States? Do you think you might be mistaken for good old G.W. if someone put the right kind of wig on you? If yes, this is for you!

No acting experience required, just a willingness to play along.

This shoots in Toronto, Canada if someone lives far from this location, travel and accommodation will be provided. 

IF YOU KNOW OF SOMEONE, PLEASE PASS THIS ON!

Compensation if selected: $6,675.00. CAD. Buyout is based on survival of the edit and includes all lifts, edits, versions. This is a non union job.

Must be available for these Important dates:

CASTING CALL 

Production Company: GreenHouse Films Production 

Project Type: UCF BFA Short Film 

Union Status: Non-Union 

Pay Status: Unpaid Projected 

Shooting Dates: TBD 

Shooting Location: Orlando area 

Summary: A lonely girl shunned by her school finds comfort in plants and in the one friend who truly sees her. 

This is an unpaid project - copy and credit will be given to all involved. This is a non-union production. 

Character Breakdowns: 

MONOMAY: Female, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), A teen girl marked by facial scars and iris coloboma, finds purpose and comfort in tending to her beloved plants. 

JASON: Male, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), The school's "Golden Boy" athlete, hides his insecurities behind charisma. 

FAN CLUB: Any gender, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), A group of students that fawn over Jason and seek his attention.

So proud to be the Executive Producer and Casting Director on Taro O'Halloranâ€™s Short Horror Film  HUMANZEE starring Liz Bishop, Cheryl Pynn and introducing Zach Norton as Ziggy!! 

It is screening at Screamfest Horror Film Festival in Hollywood at Mannâ€™s Chinese Theatre!

sharedPost.text:
Congratulations to Taro O'Halloran of Weymouth High School Class of 2020 on the screening of his Short Horror Film Humanzee starring Liz Bishop, Cheryl Pynn and introducing Zach Norton of Weymouth at Screamfest Horror Film Festival at the @TCL Chinese Theater in Hollywood!  

I am so honored to have the titles of Executive Producer and Casting Director on this film!

The hope is someone will see it and want to develop it into a Full Length Feature Film!

I see this film bringing home some awards!

My fingers are crossed for Taroâ€™s Team!

Thank you Diane Purdy's Children's Theatre Workshop for giving me my own Stage from 9 to 49 and for letting me pass it on to John and Jake who brought Taro home from school one day and we all collaborated on multiple video productions with Dianeâ€™s costumes for years!

Hi liebe Gruppe ,

Ich bin grade dabei eine Whatsapp Gruppe zu erstellen fÃ¼r Filmemacher, Schauspieler, Models, Musiker etc. 

Ich weiÃŸ selber wie schwer es teilweise ist neue Kontakte zu knÃ¼pfen oder Schauspieler fÃ¼r ein Projekt zu finden.

Ich selber bin nur in Musikvideos oder Reels zu sehen, mÃ¶chte aber dennoch eine Community erschaffen die sich gegenseitig unterstÃ¼tzt und nach dem Motto : "Ich helf dir, du hilfst mir" handelt.

Wir selber suchen fÃ¼r Musikvideos auch immer neue Schauspieler, Mitwirkende, Interessierte oder auch AnfÃ¤nger die sich noch nicht so "trauen."

Mal ist es der einschÃ¼chternd aussehende TÃ¼rsteher, mal das hÃ¼bsche blonde MÃ¤del von nebenan und mal der elegant gekleidete Ã¤ltere Herr mit Zeitung unter dem Arm. 

Haben sehr gute Reichweite auf Instagram und Youtube und gute Kontakte vieles mÃ¶glich zu machen.

Ich selber komme aus dem Raum Hamburg. 

Vielleicht finden sich hier schon fÃ¼r das nÃ¤chste Projekt coole Leute die Lust haben was zu bewegen. 

Wer Lust hat sich in der Gruppe zu integrieren darf mir gerne schreiben oder kommentieren , ich nehme dann Kontakt zu euch auf. 

Liebe GrÃ¼ÃŸe

items.text:
**INDIAN / PAKISTANI ACTING TALENT WANTED**

**Must be London Based** - for a **PROFIT SHARE **fringe theatre production running 31st March to 4th April in South Kensington, London (see image).  

**ROLES CURRENTLY AVAILABLE:**
* **ZAINAB (FEMALE/ 50s-60s) - **a fiercely charismatic Daily-Mail reading matriarch (Punjabi accent) * 
* **IMRAN (MALE/ 30s-40s) - **a young father working as a corporate accountant (Burnley accent, can coach)
* **RANIA (FEMALE/ 20s-30s) - **Imran's rebellious wife (Burnley or Punjabi accent - talent also needs to be able to sing) 
* **SAMIR (MALE/ 30s-40s) - **a heavily Anglicised London surgeon (RP) ** **
* **FATHER (MALE/ 60s-70s) - **Zainab's intelligent, devoted and long-suffering husband* 

* Zainab and Father talent are additionally paid Equity Minimum for a day's filming work

**Please email the director on ***reelpeoplefilms@hotmail.com*** for audition pieces and any further information. **Please note that this is a profit-share fringe production and renumeration (other than the filming aspect) depends on ticket sales.

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 1st week in November 2025 (date tbc). For actors based in the London area.

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  25-35, 5â€™ 6â€+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of Â£300 for 15 hours. 

BACKGROUND MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 25-35, 5â€™ 6â€+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for Â£150 for 7 hours. 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

Casting Call: 

We are looking to cast an older Hispanic female for a commercial on Monday, 10/13, morning!

This would be an English speaking role. Call time is 9:30AM in and out within an hour or so. 

The talent should send in a self-tape in English with the script I have attached below. You do not need to memorize it and only need to recite the lines.

Contact me directly to submit your audition.

items.text:
@reddybry8films  presents THE HOLLOW concept art short film. A hiker stumbles into a haunted trail pursued by a malicious entity, fighting to escape the chaos. Conceptualized from the screenplay by Bharad Reddy, tackles storytelling in 3-acts visually with warm Greens, Blues and Greys representing the character's arc. Cast- JACOB MANANQUIL Story/Director/Editor/Producer-BHARAD REDDY

https://youtu.be/bVQf2tCT-z8

https://youtu.be/bVQf2tCT-z8?si=R9EnCrajHl0GIwY1

Appreciate any thoughts or feedback!

ACTORS & CREW & LOCATIONS WANTED â€“ NO-BUDGET GRADUATION FILM (English / Multilingual)

I am Nadja, 26, nearing the completion of my acting degree at Cours Florent (Macromedia) in Berlin, and I am looking for ambitious people for **IN FRONT OF** and **BEHIND** the camera.

**Shooting Period:** November 1st â€“ November 5th in Berlin

**Budget:** None, however, we have launched a Crowdfunding campaign to create a high-quality short film (max. 15min) that will be submitted to international festivals.

The short film explores a theme that has preoccupied me my entire life: my cultural identity. Am I German? Am I Polish? Can I be both and unite these parts? How much do I owe my parents, who sacrificed so much to enable a better life for me? The film is about four people caught between tradition and their own path, struggling with what the right way forward is. The film will illuminate Polish, Vietnamese, Turkish, and German culture.

**Casting: Roles Still to be Filled (1/2 â€“ 1 shooting day per role)**

**Anna's Father (Jerzy)**

Mid-50s â€“ Mid-60s; Must speak **Polish**

The Polish immigrant (blue-collar background) who works in a skillful, crafty trade. Driven by the high educational aspirations common among Polish migrants in Germany, he relentlessly pushed Anna toward the *Gymnasium* track and high-status academic success. Must convey **conflicted pride** and strict, yet wounded, authority.

**Linh's Mother (Hoa)**

Mid-50s â€“ Mid-60s; Must speak **Vietnamese**

She is **stern and formidable** and places great importance on external appearance and family honor. Her strictness stems from a deep-seated fear that Linh's assimilation will lead to disrespect for the ancestors and personal instability. She **micromanages Linh's appearance**, demanding conservative dress and traditional feminine conduct. 

**Onur's Mother**

Approx. 60; Must speak **Turkish**

Her lifeâ€™s priority is the **continuation of the family lineage**, viewing marriage and children as the absolute purpose of life and success. She is completely **oblivious to Onur's true sexuality** and confronts him with a young woman she considers "perfect." Must convey powerful, traditional authority mixed with subtle, genuine softness.

**Onur's Aunt (Leman)**

Approx. 50; Must speak **Turkish**

Onurâ€™s charismatic and modern aunt, who serves as a vital contrast to the Mother. Leman is wittier, more open, and has a less rigid approach to life in the diaspora. She represents a more assimilated perspective and offers a relaxed energy that provides a potential emotional refuge from family pressure.

**Chris**

Approx. 30 â€“ 35; Scene involves **light intimacy** (NO nudity or partial nudity!)

An **athletic, highly attractive businessman** who operates in Annaâ€™s world of luxury and efficiency. He is polished, charismatic, and carries the effortless confidence of someone who could model formal attire. Initially perceived as a "sex-only" casual date, Chris is actually calm and emotionally perceptive, pushing for a **genuine connection** after six months of casual encounters.

**Crew and Location Search**

We are also looking for comprehensive help on set and in post-production.

**Location Search:**
* We primarily seek a large apartment with an **open-plan kitchen/living area** where we can film the main scene.
* For 1 scene, we are looking for a **Vietnamese restaurant** where we could potentially film for a few hours **BEFORE** the shop opens. No extras or food are needed, just the interior of the restaurant.
* An apartment with a **balcony** where we can film a scene with three people (ideally a *Plattenbau* setting).

If interested, please send an email to: [lostintranslationproduction@gmail.com](mailto:lostintranslationproduction@gmail.com)  or [info@nadja-gallera.de](mailto:info@nadja-gallera.de)

Thank you very much for your attention and help.

Best regards!

EDIT: Apologies for a small typo. First full performance is 23rd of November, not December. That would be silly! Amended.

CHRISTMAS CASTING CALL â€“ ENSEMBLE CAST and GROTTO ELVES

 

Seeking talented performers for this yearâ€™s production of The Magical Christmas Adventure â€” a multi-award-winning live performance and immersive attraction based near Newbury, Berkshire. The production combines the best of pantomime with interactive entertainment, inviting audiences to become part of the story.

With an all-new show for 2025, we are casting for principal roles to join our cast. Each tour runs for approximately 2 hours, with groups departing every 10 minutes â€” up to 48 tours per day.

 

Salary:

Â£15.00 hourly rate

Accommodation will be included

Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner are all provided for you.

 

Location: Headley, Berkshire

Dates:

Rehearsal from 18th November

Soft Launch 22th November

1st full performance day 23rd November

Last performance day 24th December

Approx 22 days in total

 

ROLES:

 

GRAND MASTER TOY MAKER

Santa's most trusted elf and the head of toy production at the North Pole.

 

SNOWFLAKE

In charge of keeping all the snowballs at the Ice Castle ready for battle whenever needed.

 

SPARKLE

A friendly, bubbly, energetic, and knowledgeable elf who welcomes guests to the North Pole.

 

GROTTO ELF

You'll be a bubbly, charismatic personality meeting families to take them to and stay with them doing their meeting with Santa.

 

If you would like to join us on this magical adventure, please email your CV, headshot and covering letter to [mike@themagicalchristmasadventure.co.uk](mailto:mike@themagicalchristmasadventure.co.uk)

 

[www.themagicalchristmasadventure.co.uk](http://www.themagicalchristmasadventure.co.uk)

Performance dates: Sat 17th Jan 2026(afternoon and eve) and Sun 18th Jan 2026 (afternoon only);

Rehearsal days; Monday 7pm whole cast usually; Thursday eve selected scenes.

Valley Theatreâ€™s traditional panto has become legendary in the area. As a community theatre we pride ourselves on keeping the prices family friendly without compromising on the quality. **Casting Call UBC Student Film "Sick Days"**

**Non Union, Unpaid, IMDB Credit. **

  Sick Days follows an adventurous, immigrant child who dares to indulge in his fascination of the outdoors despite his own fragile immune system, and his protective single mother's wishes to shield him from the nasty parts of the world â€” both micro and macroscopic.

**Simon- Lead**

6 to 10, Male, Korean. Bilingual preferred

A timid and optimistic child quick to follow rules but ever curious to break them.

**Holly- Lead**

30s, female, korean. Fluent in Korean

A paranoid yet tender helicopter parent, shielding her son from the world.

**Anthony- Supporting**

6 to 10, Fun loving, extroverted kid, searching for camaraderie in a lonely new city.

Submit a Headshot and any supporting materials (demo-reel or self-tapes) to sickdays.film@gmail.com

Specific Shoot dates are tentative, but will either be December 6-8, or 13-15.

items.summary:
**Casting Call UBC Student Film "Sick Days"**

**Non Union, Unpaid, IMDB Credit. **

  Sick Days follows an adventurous, immigrant child who dares to indulge in his fascination of the outdoors despite his own fragile immune system, and his protective single mother's wishes to shield him from the nasty parts of the world â€” both micro and macroscopic.

**Simon- Lead**

6 to 10, Male, Korean. Bilingual preferred

A timid and optimistic child quick to follow rules but ever curious to break them.

**Holly- Lead**

30s, female, korean. Fluent in Korean

A paranoid yet tender helicopter parent, shielding her son from the world.

**Anthony- Supporting**

6 to 10, Fun loving, extroverted kid, searching for camaraderie in a lonely new city.

Submit a Headshot and any supporting materials (demo-reel or self-tapes) to sickdays.film@gmail.com

Specific Shoot dates are tentative, but will either be December 6-8, or 13-15.

items.text:
Actors (non-union) needed for a documentary regarding Elizabeth Johnson Jr who was the last convicted witch to be exonerated from the 1692 Salem Witchcraft Trials.

The ideal actor for Elizabeth will have strawberry blond or slight red hair, be of average height and able to portray early 20s.

Two additional actors will be needed as elders (40-60) who arrest her and walk her away.

The shoot will require one day in early November or early December on north of Boston. Pay will be negotiated.  Access to a late 17th century costume is a plus. Send headshot, resume and November, December availability to SalemHistoricalTours@gmail.com
